{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Make your apps even better through improved integration with Photos on macOS. We’ll dive deep into the Photos Project Extension API that was introduced in macOS High Sierra and update you on what’s new. You’ll also learn best practices for handling file promises and image URLs to better handle drag & drop from Photos to your app.","type":"text"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2018\/505\/","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex"}},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-505-Integrating-with-Photos-on-macOS"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference"}]},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Related Sessions"},{"type":"links","style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-505-Whats-New-in-Photos-APIs","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-203-Whats-New-in-Cocoa"]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-505-integrating-with-photos-on-macos"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC18","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Integrating with Photos on macOS"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18"]]},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-505-Whats-New-in-Photos-APIs":{"type":"topic","title":"What’s New in Photos APIs","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Learn all about newest APIs in Photos on iOS and macOS, providing better integration and new possibilities for your app. We’ll discuss simplifications to accessing the Photos library through UIImagePickerController, explore additions to PhotoKit to support new media types, and share all the details of the new Photos Project Extensions which enable you to bring photo services to Photos for Mac.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-505-whats-new-in-photos-apis","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-505-Whats-New-in-Photos-APIs"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-203-Whats-New-in-Cocoa":{"abstract":[{"text":"macOS brings many new enhancements such as automatic window tabbing, enhanced color reproduction, and improved presentation of right-to-left languages. Get introduced to new APIs for these features and more, such as NSGridView and NSMeasurement. Learn about new conventions for APIs in Swift and Objective-C. This is your first stop to discover exciting new features in Cocoa sessions throughout the week.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-203-whats-new-in-cocoa","title":"What’s New in Cocoa","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-203-Whats-New-in-Cocoa"},"WWDC18.jpeg":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC18.jpeg","type":"image","alt":null},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","